---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
---

<Base title="About — Sơn Lê">
  <Nav active="about" />

  <div class="page-wrap">
    <div class="page-prompt mono text-3">./about</div>
    <h1 class="page-title">Sơn Lê</h1>

    <div class="about-section">
      <h2 class="about-h2">VC → Operator → Builder</h2>
      <p>
        I spent the first chapter of my career writing checks. Sat on the other side of the table from founders,
        evaluated bets, learned what makes a venture work — and more importantly, what doesn't.
      </p>
      <p>
        Then I switched sides. Spent years as an operator, running companies instead of judging them.
        Cashed out some reputation along the way. Learned that building is harder than betting, and infinitely more honest.
      </p>
      <p>
        Now I build. In Saigon, with a fleet of AI agents as my operating system.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="about-section">
      <h2 class="about-h2">What I'm doing now</h2>
      <p>
        Founder of <a href="https://perfeat.org" class="accent-link">Perfeat.org ↗</a> — a private food diary where every meal
        gets a rating and a page. Running multiple ventures under an AI-native holding company OS.
        Writing about what I notice along the way.
      </p>
      <p>
        My thesis: the marginal cost of building software is approaching zero. The bottleneck isn't code —
        it's judgment, taste, and the ability to decide what matters. I'm building systems that amplify
        those human decisions instead of replacing them.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="about-section">
      <h2 class="about-h2">How I work</h2>
      <p>
        I run a fleet of specialized AI agents, each with its own role, voice, and lane. They coordinate
        through a shared knowledge graph, write to a common brain, and ship independently. I don't manage
        them — I steer them.
      </p>
      <p>
        This is OS V1. Every venture, every decision, every piece of durable knowledge lives in the same
        memory substrate. The agents handle the execution. I handle the direction.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="about-cta">
      <a href="/projects" class="btn-primary">See what I'm building</a>
      <a href="/series" class="btn-ghost">Read the writing</a>
    </div>

    <div class="about-contact">
      <div class="mono text-3">Find me elsewhere</div>
      <div class="about-socials">
        <a href="mailto:tuanson.le03@gmail.com" class="about-social mono accent">tuanson.le03@gmail.com ↗</a>
        <a href="https://x.com/toilaleson" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="about-social mono accent">X / Twitter ↗</a>
        <a href="https://github.com/toilaleson" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="about-social mono accent">GitHub ↗</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Base>
